  07 Jul 2006; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org>
  lilypond-2.8.0-r1.ebuild:
  remove non-existent app-text/ghostscript-afpl dep

  28 Apr 2006; Jason Wever <weeve@gentoo.org> lilypond-2.8.0-r1.ebuild:
  Re-added ~sparc keyword as it went missing.

  05 Apr 2006; Stefan Schweizer <genstef@gentoo.org>
  lilypond-2.8.0-r1.ebuild:
  Change virtual/ghostscript to || ( ) RDEPEND, bug 128887 thanks to Jean
  Br√©fort <jean.brefort@normalesup.org>

  29 Mar 2006; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> lilypond-2.0.3.ebuild,
  lilypond-2.2.4.ebuild, lilypond-2.2.6.ebuild, lilypond-2.4.2.ebuild,
  lilypond-2.5.2.ebuild, lilypond-2.8.0-r1.ebuild:
  More testing shows that lilypond-2.8.0 will build with tetex-3, so don't
  restrict to tetex-2 for that version.  Repair my broken sed expression in the
  other ebuilds (was subbing pfa->PFA twice instead of doing pfb->PFB in the
  second case)

  28 Mar 2006; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> lilypond-2.0.3.ebuild,
  lilypond-2.2.4.ebuild, lilypond-2.2.6.ebuild, lilypond-2.4.2.ebuild,
  lilypond-2.5.2.ebuild, lilypond-2.8.0-r1.ebuild:
  Restrict older lilyponds to tetex-2 which provides /usr/bin/inimf #92040.
  sed makefiles so that mftrace-1.1.x can be used in place of mftrace-1.0.x
  #90334

  27 Mar 2006; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> lilypond-2.8.0-r1.ebuild:
  addwrite /root/.PfaEdit workaround #127723

*lilypond-2.8.0-r1 (27 Mar 2006)

  27 Mar 2006; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> -lilypond-2.8.0.ebuild,
  +lilypond-2.8.0-r1.ebuild:
  Fix support of USE=emacs. Fix sandbox issue when the same version of
  lilypond is re-installed

  26 Mar 2006; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> lilypond-2.0.3.ebuild,
  lilypond-2.2.4.ebuild, lilypond-2.2.6.ebuild, lilypond-2.4.2.ebuild,
  lilypond-2.5.2.ebuild, lilypond-2.8.0.ebuild:
  Older lilypond requires older mftrace, doesn't build with mftrace-1.1*. Run
  emake with LC_ALL=C so that mftrace doesn't complain about using iconv

*lilypond-2.8.0 (26 Mar 2006)

